markets.title: Will the US emit more than 430 million metric tons of **carbon dioxide** in December 2021?
markets.subtitle: >430m mt
markets.rules_primary: If the estimated US carbon dioxide emissions from energy consumption according to the EIA for December 2021 exceed 430 million metric tons, then the market resolves to Yes.
markets.rules_secondary: To access the Underlying, please visit Table 11.1 of the Monthly Energy Review published by the Energy Information Administration. Please see CO2 in the Rulebook for more details and the binding Terms and Conditions.

markets.title: Will the US emit more than 390 million metric tons of **carbon dioxide** in November 2021?
markets.subtitle: >390m mt
markets.rules_primary: If the estimated US carbon dioxide emissions from energy consumption according to the EIA for November 2021 exceed 390 million metric tons, then the market resolves to Yes.
markets.rules_secondary:
To access the Underlying, please visit Table 11.1 of the Monthly Energy Review published by the Energy Information Administration. These instructions on how to access the Underlying are provided for convenience only and are not part of the binding Terms and Conditions of the Contract. Please see CO2 in the Rulebook for more details and the binding Terms and Conditions.

The market will close and expire at the sooner of the first day following the release of the data for November 2021, which is scheduled for February 24, 2022, and March 17, 2022.
